                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.811/7–2545</note>
                <head>No. 1375<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Proposal by the British Delegation</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1375fn1">Submitted at a meeting of the Subcommittee on
                        Inland Waterways, July 27. See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_453">p. 453</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract<note n="2" xml:id="d1375fn2">For the other
                            paragraphs of this proposal, see <ref target="#d759">document No.
                                759</ref>.</note>]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-27">July 27,
                            1945</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Draft Proposal by the British Delegation</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">International Inland Waterways</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>It was also agreed that the principle of free and unrestricted navigation should
                    be applied to the whole of the Straits between the Black Sea and the Aegean Sea,
                    and that in furtherance of this principle the Montreux Convention of 1936 should
                    be abrogated by the proper regular procedure and replaced by a new international
                    agreement. This agreement would affirm the principle of free and unrestricted
                    navigation of the Straits by warships and merchant ships, in peace and <gloss
                        target="#t_War1">war</gloss>, and would be guaranteed, for their part, by
                    the Three Powers.</p>
            </div>
